Text.SourceString: Well, hello to yo–//ACHOOOOOO!//<portrait=annoyed>Ugh… Spring. Not the best time to move here.
By the way, I’m <NPCName>Char</>–//<portrait=surprised>ACHOOO!
Well, hello to you too! You must be new here.
I hope you like Coral Island. See you around!
The recycling center been here since…umm…
I can’t remember, for the life of me.//Tell you what, I’ll mail you if it comes back to me.
I don’t want to be rude, but I wonder what you put in those pockets of yours.//<portrait=happy>They always seem so full.
That reminds me. I forgot to recycle yesterday.
I’m all for farming. I think it’s an excellent activity for both body and mind.
You know what?//<portrait=normal>I hope more people will get out of their houses and do some farming… Or gardening. Get up and sweat it out!
Don’t you feel good after a good farming session, <PlayerName>$player</>?
That’s what sunshine and physical activity does for you, my friend.//It gets the endorphins going – your feel-good pheromones.
Dehydration is a real thing. Your body’s mostly water and can’t work right without it. So remember to stay hydrated and drink plenty!
Sorry, I often sound stuffy in the morning.//But it usually clears up later.
It’s important to be aware of our allergies.//You really don’t want to discover an allergy accidentally.

Especially not when you’re in the middle of a hot date.//Take a bite of that clam, then a rash suddenly breaks out and your lips start to swell.//<portrait=happy>NOT based on personal experience… *winks*
Work hard. But, more importantly, work smart.//Don’t overexert yourself and pass out, or you’ll be billed for a medical emergency.
We don’t charge an outrageous amount though.//Just enough to cover the cost.
Health is wealth… Don’t forget that, kid!//Your money means nothing if you’re not healthy enough to enjoy them.
New fashion trends are cool…but on other people.//I’m pretty comfortable with my style, so I’m sticking with it.
I enjoy the conformity of fashion.//In a way, it gives me a sense of belonging.
Even if it’s just in the way I dress. Slacks and polos.
I wear my crimson khakis when I’m feeling daring.//<portrait=happy>Have you seen me in them?//<portrait=normal>It’s quite the outfit, I’ve been told.
*off-key singing*
People here are open-minded. They’ve never held anything against me.
I feel very safe here… This is home to me.
Live and let live, I say.//As people, I think we should avoid harming others and afford each other the same respect and dignity that we expect ourselves.
But that’s just my opinion.
I have this ritual that I’ve been doing for who knows how long.//So usually, on Saturdays, I like to make burritos and keep the leftovers for Sunday’s lunch.//Isn’t that fun?
It’s okay to let loose on special occasions.//You just need to remember not to get carried away.
Ha ha… What can I say? I really should heed my own medical advice sometimes.//<portrait=happy>Some things are just easier said than done, especially when burritos are involved!
It’s important get your health checked regularly.//If something’s wrong, it can be picked up early.
Your mental health is just as important as your physical health.//If either is suffering, it can be catastrophic to you.
I don’t mean to scare you or anything. Just telling the truth!
We need to start talking about mental health more, to erase the social stigma around it.
And, as a result, we can detect them easier and faster.//<portrait=happy>Early detection is the root of a successful health plan, you see.
Having a hobby can help you relax and help you work more efficiently in the long run.//So, if you don’t already have a hobby, maybe start reading or pick up a fishing rod.
Is my hair messy?
Oh, you said lazy. I thought you said my hair was MESSY.//<portrait=annoyed>Don’t scare me like that! No, I’m not being lazy. Just taking a break.

One day, not long from now, my hair will be gone. So, I’m trying to hold on to each strand as long as I can.//Nothing’s wrong with going bald. I just can’t imagine how hot it would be under the sun, that’s all.
I’ll need to cover my head in sunscreen when I’m bald…
Or I could always wear a hat.
<NpcName>Scott</>’s a bit messy and leaves things all over the place…//<portrait=normal>But, other than that, he’s a decent housemate.
That said, he often walks straight into doors. Not just screen doors, regular solid ones too.//<portrait=annoyed>It’s amazing how successful he is, given his clumsiness.
I’m glad that everyone here is given equal access to health care.
Access to health care is a basic human need.//So, I don’t think wealth should restrict whether or not someone gets it.
We’re lucky to never have to worry about health care.//<portrait=concerned>It’s a luxury in some parts of the world… Unfair, I know.
Our clinic only charges for emergency services…//And even with that, we’re highly subsidized by the government, so everyone pays a share of what they can afford.
During my many years working in the clinic, I have never once turned away anyone in need.//That’s not what we’re about here.
I could go for a burrito right now.//<portrait=normal>Maybe some strawberries later.
I make sure to match my tie to my hair. It’s hard to choose the right shade sometimes, but thank goodness, I got that sorted out.
It’s hard to be seen next to <NpcName>Yuri</>, because she’s so green… Very garish, if you ask me.
Milk gives me an upset stomach, so I try to avoid it. Honestly, I would rather not drink it at all.
I’m trying to reduce my dairy intake. But some things are harder to cut out than others.
The last time I went out dancing? Hmm… It had to have been last week.
You seem interested in my dancing schedule. You’re not going to take me out dancing, are ya?
’Cause I’m not going to say no. *chuckles*
Today is not a good day to go to the tavern. Trust me!//It’s so busy there on the weekend. Phew!
There are so many people in the tavern. There’s no room to dance.//What’s the point of going if I’m not going to dance, right? I prefer to go there on Fridays.
I popped into the tavern to see if anyone was there, but then just left. I wasn’t really feeling it today.
*mumbling incomprehensible gibberish*
Hey, I'm most certainly not mumbling incomprehensible gibberish!//I was trying to recall the names of the medicines that I need to restock.
Uh oh…here it comes…spring allergies.
Hold on a-//<portrait=surprised>ACHOO!//<portrait=normal>What I was saying was-//<portrait=surprised>ACHOO!//<portrait=normal>Okay, I think I'm good now. Where were we?
I’m staying away from milk.//<portrait=annoyed>It doesn’t agree with my stomach.
Life must be exciting for farmers like you right now.
Oh, with the new season and all.//<portrait=happy>It’s an ideal time for farming, no?
Hmm... I would apply more sunscreen in about an hour if I were you.//<portrait=normal>Better safe than sorry, I always say.
I’m closing my windows for the whole season.
I know what you’re gonna say. I should probably take allergy medicine, right? It makes me really drowsy…//Haven’t found the right one, probably.
I always change clothes as soon as I get home.// You don’t want to sleep with that pollen sticking to your clothes and hair and stuff. *shivers*
I’m so glad <NPCName>Yuri</> is here. She’s made of iron, that one.//I would’ve been miserable running the clinic alone with all this pollen flying around.
I like the weather, but Spring’s gotta be at the bottom of my list of favorite seasons.
My allergies are like clockwork, <PlayerName>$player</>. As soon as it’s the first of Spring, that’s it for me.
I feel like myself again! No more endless sniffling!
I can open my windows again now the pollen has calmed down.//Nothing beats waking up in the fresh air.
I have to say…hot weather isn’t my thing.//It puffs up my hair like cotton candy.
It’s good that more people are out and about in Summer.//As long as we don’t forget the sunscreen, right?
The humidity isn’t helping my hair at all.//Yours is fine, though. How come? What shampoo do you use?
People can call me annoying all they want, but I’m going to keep reminding them about sunscreen. Especially in this blazing Summer sun.
I’ve already had to treat a few people for sunburn.//<portrait=surprised>Won’t name names, <PlayerName>$player</>, patient–doctor confidentiality and all that.
Daisies don’t make me sneeze too much unless I get really close. So I just stay away from where they grow.
I just love Fall. There’s all the warming comfort food, and it’s not too hot or cold outside.//It’s perfect.
The best thing about Fall is definitely sweet potato chips.//Sure, I could get them in other seasons, but they’re just better in the Fall, you know?
Nothing like the crisp Fall air for enjoying some sweet potato chips.//<portrait=annoyed>I wish I had some now…
I’m better suited to colder weather, I think.//Not too many mosquitos, and I just wake up refreshed!
Have you gotten your flu shot yet?//Winter is next week, you know.
Are you excited for the Harvest Festival, <PlayerName>$player</>? Personally, I can’t wait.
<NPCName>Yuri</> and I are usually pretty busy this season.//The townsfolk always need us for something other, whether it’s treating a cold or patching them up after a slip on the ice.

Take care of yourself this season, <PlayerName>$player</>. Winter weather can be harsh on our health…especially with less and less sunshine.//And I’m not just talking about the flu or the common cold. Winter blues is a real thing.
Another Winter’s almost passed.//Not many flu cases this year… I’m very grateful.
I open my windows first thing in the morning.//I like to let the cold air in.
You need to layer up when you leave the house…especially in Winter.//Another tip: wash your hands when you get home. Some viruses thrive in dry, cold conditions.
I’m looking forward to the New Year’s Eve Festival. Are you? I can’t wait for the present exchange and to eat all the good food.//<NPCName>Bree</> is an amazing host!
The heat is messing with my routine.
This heat is so annoying… I’m not feeling like myself.
I think the heat is getting to me. I feel annoyed.
The sun is hammering down on me today… How am I supposed to work when it’s like this?
I feel like I’m in an oven! Where’s a nice cool breeze when you need one?//My hair’s gone nuts, as well. I just can’t seem to catch a break in this weather!
Oh, finally, a cool breeze!
Wow, seems like my hair matches this season…
It’s bright yet soothing, warm yet refreshing, crisp yet soft, and – just like me – full of warmth.
I guess farmers like your good self must be busy this season, eh?
What do you mean, why? It’s fall. Some even call it the harvest season.
I'm in a melancholy mood.
I blame the snow.
I'm in a melancholy mood.
I blame the snow. Well, at least the dinner party is coming up soon, eh?
All this snow must be challenging for people in your trade.//Farming and the snowy season… Tough business.
I’m noticing less variety in the fresh produce at Sam’s, compared to other seasons.
Time passes so quickly these days… Just like falling raindrops.//There one second, gone the next.
I don’t think I’ll go out and about today.
Rainy days like this provide a rare opportunity to catch up on some paperwork.
I think I’ll stop by the tavern after work to warm up.//On rainy days like this, I bet you the tavern is busier than ever.
People just don’t like to walk around in the rain, and I guess they’re bored sitting around at home.
Want to know what’s fun to do in this type of weather? Work.
Is my hair okay? I think the rain messed it up on the way here.
Is <NpcName>Millie</> looking this way? How do I look?
Fancy seeing you here this late, <PlayerName>$player</>.
What? Why are you looking at me like that?
Do I have something in my hair?
I don’t think I’ll go out today.
It’s a good time to catch up on some paperwork.
I have to go…
It’s late.
I’ll be out late today. I don’t want to be home all by myself…//I’m feeling quite lonely.
Time flies on snowy days.
Want to know what’s fun to do in this type of weather? Work. Get your body moving and warm up.
I hope it stops snowing soon. It messes up my hair.
Am I out late? Um… I suppose the loneliness hits differently when you’re home alone on a snowy day.
I haven’t felt this down for a while…
I blame the cold weather.
Let me tell you something... the loneliness hits differently when you’re home alone on a snowy day.
Let me tell you something... the loneliness hits differently when you’re home alone on a snowy day.//It makes you not want to be at home.
Farmer <PlayerName>$player</>, need some more vitamins?

Don’t shame a man for trying to sell his products, <PlayerName>$player</>.//<portrait=normal>Vitamins help you and they help me at the same time. I don’t know what you’re talking about.//It doesn’t sound shady to me at all.
Are you okay? You look flushed and sweaty.//<portrait=normal>I recommend a dose of medicine.
What are you doing here, <PlayerName>$player</>?//<portrait=surprised>You okay?
Watch your step! Slippery floor!
We disinfect the clinic to international standards, especially after emergencies.//Excellent hygiene is critical in health care.
It’s too bright here sometimes. It’s hard for me to nap.
Joking. *chuckles*
Remember to put on your sunscreen.
Ahh… I woke up this morning to the realization that this island is full of clean air and good people.
It’s gonna be a good day, I can feel it!
If you get cut or scraped, wash it right away with running water.//This will clean the wound.
*sneezes* You never know when allergies will hit.
I can’t believe people want to drill oil here, of all places…//<portrait=normal>This island is beautiful!//Before the oil spill happened anyway.
I hope you don’t overfeed pet.//Playing with our pets when they’re bored is much better than just giving them treats.
You’re right, I don’t have any pets.//<portrait=normal>But that doesn’t mean I don’t know anything about them.
*sneezes* Oh, sorry. The flowers. This season…really gets to me… *sneezes*
I’m okay… Thanks!
Come here often?
Glad to see you here, <PlayerName>$player</>.
Two drinks and I’m done. Anything more and it’s hangover city for me the next day.

Ah, who am I kidding? My hair isn’t this bright.//I’ve got gray hair, <PlayerName>$player</>! That’s why I keep revamping the color.//<portrait=concerned>Oh, jeez. Do youngsters still say “revamping”?
They don’t say “youngsters” anymore, do they?//<portrait=concerned>My age is showing.
Never once in my life have I come here intending to buy anything, but somehow I always buy something I don’t need.
If my pollen allergy weren’t so bad, I would buy some flowers.
There are plenty of wild fruits around here.
Oh, what am I reading? Just some medical journals and fashion magazines.
Just chatting away with <NpcName>Suki</>.//Besides, it’s too hot for me to be outside.
I can’t believe how bright it is outside today…//If it weren’t for that ice-cold wind, you’d think it was summer!
Ugh, I don’t think I put on enough sunscreen today. I hope they have extra!
<NpcName>Sunny</> always tries to talk me into fishing. Heh heh, funny guy.
Nice to see you here, <PlayerName>$player</>!
I found wild berries near the lighthouse the other day!
I’ve yet to see this place packed.
You’re not looking for me, are you, <PlayerName>$player</>?//Because I’m off duty right now.
I’m here to make sure <NpcName>Millie</> is doing well.
Err… I mean, to make sure her tasks are done on time.
I’m checking out a couple of books today to read over the next week.
I think I’ll head back home after this.//I feel exhausted.
